==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sambur
<hw>Sam"bur</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Hind.
<ets>s⟦amac⟧mbar</ets>, <ets>s⟦amac⟧bar</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>An East Indian deer (<spn>Rusa Aristotelis</spn>) having a mane on
its neck. Its antlers have but three prongs. Called also
<altname>gerow</altname>. The name is applied to other species of the
genus <gen>Rusa</gen>, as the Bornean sambur (<spn>Rusa
equina</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

